15. CI/CD integration
- Works with Jenkins, GitLab, Azure DevOps
- Automated tests run on code push
- Faster feedback & bug detection
- Improves software quality, release speed

16. Choosing IDE vs WebDriver
- IDE: beginners, learning, quick prototypes
- WebDriver: real projects, precise control, complex scenarios

17. Why pick WebDriver over Grid?
- WebDriver: write & execute scripts, simulate user actions
- Grid: parallel execution, cross-browser on multiple machines
- WebDriver = test creation; Grid = scaling tests

18. Advanced user interactions in WebDriver
- Actions class: Drag & Drop, Mouse Hover, Keyboard Actions
- Handles file uploads & complex behavior
